    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.26.19-20_0001"/>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">19</fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>1/29/58</dateline>
                
                    <salute>Dear Dr. and Mrs. Neihardt</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>No apologies are necessary &#8212; we realize how popular and busy you are. Just being in your presence &#8212; even for a few minutes &#8212; is an enlightening experience. Besides the people we meet at your home are always so interesting. We don't meet too many interesting conversationalists here.</p>
                
                <p>One or the other of us has been ill since we last saw you. In fact we have been plagued with illness since Thanksgiving. Even our dog had distemper and had to be put away. He was such a sweet animal and had such a distinct personality. It was like losing one of the children. The past few days we have been enjoying fair health, though Cindy is coughing again tonight.</p>
                
                <p>I am very interested in the prospect of fishing your ponds and intend to come up when the ice has melted. Is it all right if I bring a friend?</p>
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.26.19-20_0002"/>
                
                <p>I will bring my Luger along and we can test it. I have only fired it 9 or 10 times and am anxious to use it a little more.</p>
                
                <p>The first semester is over and I can truthfully say I will be glad when the second one is over too. It is no fun teaching children who are not interested in school.</p>
                
                <p>News is <unclear>scarce</unclear> here, so I'll close&#8212;</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Love from all of us &#8212;</salute>
                
                    <signed>Jack, Willa, Sally + Cindy</signed>
                
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>[John <hi rend="caps">O.</hi> Roberts, Jr.</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>1122 <hi rend="caps">N.</hi> Harrison</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Kirkwood 22, Mo.]</addrLine>
                    </address>
                </closer>
                
